1. Definitions. The below words have the following meanings:
1.1. “Account(s)” means the credit line extended to Company by Issuer. An Account may be evidenced by a plastic Card or an account number. 
1.2. “Account User” means Company or any other entity or individual authorized by Company to use Account or Cards. 
1.3. “Annual Percentage Rate” or “APR” means the cost of your credit expressed as a yearly rate.
1.4. “Billing Cycle” means the time interval between the dates of your regular billing statements. Your first Billing Cycle may be less than one month. All credit terms, including minimum interest charges, will apply in each Billing Cycle including the first Billing Cycle.
1.5. “Business Day” means any day other than a Saturday, Sunday, or other day on which banking institutions in Utah are generally authorized or required by law or executive order to close.
1.6. “Card” means a credit card provided by Issuer which is used to access Company’s Account.
1.7. “Closing Date” means the last date of a Billing Cycle.
1.8. “Company” means the corporation, partnership, Limited Liability Company, proprietorship or other business entity that has applied for, or accepted an Account with Issuer.
1.9. “Controls” are a set of authorization tools designed to assist Company with managing purchases.
1.10. “Daily Periodic Rate” is 1/365th of the corresponding Annual Percentage Rate (1/366th of the corresponding Annual Percentage Rate in a leap year).
1.11. “DID” or “DIN” mean the identification number associated with an Account User or Card.
1.12. “Interest Charge” means the cost of credit payable by you on the Account as a dollar amount. 
1.13. “Fleet or Business Contact Person” means the person you select who is authorized to provide us with the information necessary to establish and/or manage your Account(s) and Cards.
1.14. “Index” means the index used to calculate your APR as named in Section 3.7.
1.15. “Margin” is the amount added to the Index to determine your Annual Percentage Rate, expressed as a percent.
1.16. “Minimum Payment” means the minimum amount you must pay on your Account by the due date in a billing cycle, as shown on your billing statement.
1.17. “Other Charges” are charges other than Interest that may be assessed on your Account, as described in Section 3.8 below.
1.18. “Previous Balance” means the balance outstanding on your Account at the beginning of a Billing Cycle.  (It is the same amount that was shown as “Statement Balance” on the billing statement for the preceding Billing Cycle.)
1.19. “Promotional Balances” means credit lines extended by WEX Bank for introductory and other designated Purchase transactions subject to discounted fees and/or a different Daily Periodic Rate.
1.20. “Promotional Rate” means the Daily Periodic Rate applied to Promotional Balances.
1.21. “Purchase(s)” means the use of a Card or Account to buy goods or services at accepting merchants.
1.22. “Rate Chart” means the chart of Interest Rates and Fees that is part of this Credit Agreement.
1.23. “Company Credit Limit” is the amount of credit assigned to Company’s Account as established by Issuer from time to time.  This is a revolving credit limit.
1.24. “Statement Balance” is the entire balance outstanding on your Account on the Closing Date of a billing cycle, including Purchases, accrued Interest Charges and Other Charges as of such date.
1.25. “Transaction” means the use of a Card or Account to buy goods or services at accepting merchants.  
1.26. “Unauthorized Transaction” means a Transaction made on a Card or Account by any person or entity other than an Account User. 
